OL,7,F"Since then our members have voted,
OL,8,Ftime and again, for strikes. That's
OL,9,Fwhy Mark Harper, the transport
OL,10,Fsecretary, is being disingenuous when
OL,11,Fhe says that offer should have been
OL,12,Fput to members.
OL,14,F"Drivers obviously wouldn't vote for
OL,15,Findustrial action, again and again and
OL,16,Fagain, if they thought that was a good
OL,17,Foffer. They don't. That offer was dead
OL,18,Fin the water in April last year ` and
OL,19,FI think Mr Harper knows that."
